# Factor Out Views and API Modules

For view decomposition/layout decisions, use `view-architecture-pattern.mdc` as the canonical rule.

This rule keeps only the folder-level defaults:

- Page-level views live under `frontend/src/views/` with feature-local CSS where appropriate.
- `App.tsx` composes views and app-shell routing/state; avoid embedding feature-specific view logic there.
- Keep global/shared styling in shared/global style files; keep feature-specific rules inside feature view CSS.

## API Modules

The API layer lives under `frontend/src/api/`. Each domain entity gets its own file with types and methods. Shared infrastructure stays in `core.ts`.

- `core.ts` – shared `request` helper, token management (`getToken`, `setToken`, `clearToken`), auth API methods, reference-data API methods (codes, catalogues), and shared types (`AppUser`, `Code`).
- One file per domain entity (e.g. `patients.ts`) – contains all interfaces (entity, create, update, child entities) and all API methods for that entity and its children.
- `index.ts` – barrel file that re-exports everything and provides a unified `api` object.

When adding a new entity:
1. Top-level domain -> new `frontend/src/api/<domain>.ts`.
2. Child domain -> keep in parent module when tightly coupled.
3. Re-export through `frontend/src/api/index.ts` and merged `api`.
